{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_016H5ZszRiSkpaSo1FVXENM2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have everything I need. Here is the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Complete Implementation\n\nThe task has three parts:\n1. **Read the CNO-injected CA ConfigMap, compute a SHA-256 hash, and stamp it on the IstioCSR Deployment's pod template** — new file `configmaps.go`\n2. **Thread the hash through the reconciliation** — modify `install_istiocsr.go` and `deployments.go`\n3. **Add the idempotency guard** in `deploymentSpecModified` to detect annotation changes — modify `utils.go`\n4. **Watch the CNO-injected ConfigMap for changes** — modify `controller.go`\n5. **Add a constant for the annotation key** — modify `constants.go`\n6. **Add tests** — new file `configmaps_test.go`\n\n### File 1: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go` (NEW)\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n)\n\n// readTrustedCABundle reads the CNO-injected CA bundle from the operator namespace.\n// Returns the PEM bundle and any error.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) readTrustedCABundle() (string, error) {\n\tinjectionCM := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\tkey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\tName:      common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, key, injectionCM); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(\n\t\t\terr,\n\t\t\t\"failed to read CA bundle ConfigMap %q in namespace %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\t)\n\t}\n\n\tcaBundle, ok := injectionCM.Data[common.TrustedCABundleKey]\n\tif !ok || caBundle == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", nil\n\t}\n\n\treturn caBundle, nil\n}\n\n// computeCABundleHash returns the SHA-256 hash of the CA bundle PEM content.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n\n// stampCABundleHash reads the CNO-injected CA bundle, computes a content hash,\n// and returns it. Returns (\"\", nil) if the ConfigMap doesn't exist or is empty.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) stampCABundleHash() (string, error) {\n\tcaBundle, err := r.readTrustedCABundle()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to read trusted CA bundle: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif caBundle == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", nil\n\t}\n\n\treturn computeCABundleHash(caBundle), nil\n}\n```\n\n### File 2: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go` (MODIFY)\n\nAdd the new annotation constant. Insert after the `IstiocsrCAKeyName` constant (line 89):\n\n```go\n// caContentHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n// SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA bundle content. Changing the annotation\n// value triggers a rolling restart of the IstioCSR Deployment.\ncaContentHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-content-hash\"\n```\n\nThe full constants block with the addition (replace lines 83-90):\n\n```go\n\t// IstiocsrCAConfigMapName is the name of the configmap which is mounted in istiocsr container, containing the\n\t// CA certificate configured in the secret referenced in the issuer.\n\tIstiocsrCAConfigMapName = istiocsrCommonName + \"-issuer-ca-copy\"\n\n\t// IstiocsrCAKeyName is the key name holding the CA certificate in the issuer secret or the controller\n\t// CA configmap.\n\tIstiocsrCAKeyName = \"ca.crt\"\n\n\t// caContentHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n\t// SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA bundle content. Changing the annotation\n\t// value triggers a rolling restart of the IstioCSR Deployment.\n\tcaContentHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-content-hash\"\n```\n\n### File 3: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/install_istiocsr.go` (MODIFY)\n\nThread the CA bundle hash through the reconciliation, inserting between `createOrApplyCertificates` and `createOrApplyDeployments`. The full modified file:\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"maps\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/api/operator/v1alpha1\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n)\n\nfunc (r *Reconciler) reconcileIstioCSRDeployment(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, istioCSRCreateRecon bool) error {\n\tif err := validateIstioCSRConfig(istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn common.NewIrrecoverableError(err, \"%s/%s configuration validation failed\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName())\n\t}\n\n\t// if user has set custom labels to be added to all resources created by the controller\n\t// merge it with the controller's own default labels.\n\tresourceLabels := make(map[string]string)\n\tif istiocsr.Spec.ControllerConfig != nil && len(istiocsr.Spec.ControllerConfig.Labels) != 0 {\n\t\tmaps.Copy(resourceLabels, istiocsr.Spec.ControllerConfig.Labels)\n\t}\n\tmaps.Copy(resourceLabels, controllerDefaultResourceLabels)\n\n\tif err := r.createOrApplyNetworkPolicies(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile network policy resources\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.createOrApplyServices(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile service resource\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.createOrApplyServiceAccounts(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile serviceaccount resource\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.createOrApplyRBACResource(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile rbac resources\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.createOrApplyCertificates(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile certificate resource\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tcaBundleHash, err := r.stampCABundleHash()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to compute CA bundle hash\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon, caBundleHash); err != nil {\n\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile deployment resource\")\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tif addProcessedAnnotation(istiocsr) {\n\t\tif err := r.UpdateWithRetry(r.ctx, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update processed annotation to %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tr.log.V(4).Info(\"finished reconciliation of istiocsr\", \"namespace\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), \"name\", istiocsr.GetName())\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n### File 4: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` (MODIFY)\n\nTwo changes:\n1. Add `caBundleHash` parameter to `createOrApplyDeployments` and pass it to `getDeploymentObject`\n2. In `getDeploymentObject`, stamp the hash annotation on the pod template\n\n**Change 1**: `createOrApplyDeployments` signature and call (line 31):\n\nReplace:\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, istioCSRCreateRecon bool) error {\n\tdesired, err := r.getDeploymentObject(istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n```\n\nWith:\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, istioCSRCreateRecon bool, caBundleHash string) error {\n\tdesired, err := r.getDeploymentObject(istiocsr, resourceLabels, caBundleHash)\n```\n\n**Change 2**: `getDeploymentObject` signature (line 73):\n\nReplace:\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (*appsv1.Deployment, error) {\n```\n\nWith:\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, caBundleHash string) (*appsv1.Deployment, error) {\n```\n\n**Change 3**: After `updateVolumes` returns (after line 103), add the hash annotation stamping:\n\n```go\n\tif err := r.updateVolumes(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update volume %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n\t}\n\n\tif caBundleHash != \"\" {\n\t\tif deployment.Spec.Template.Annotations == nil {\n\t\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations = make(map[string]string)\n\t\t}\n\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations[caContentHashAnnotation] = caBundleHash\n\t}\n\n\treturn deployment, nil\n```\n\n### File 5: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go` (MODIFY)\n\nAdd pod template annotation comparison to `deploymentSpecModified` for the idempotency guard. After the template labels check (line 316), add an annotation check:\n\nReplace:\n```go\n\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(desired.Spec.Template.Labels, fetched.Spec.Template.Labels) ||\n\t\tlen(desired.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers) != len(fetched.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers) {\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n```\n\nWith:\n```go\n\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(desired.Spec.Template.Labels, fetched.Spec.Template.Labels) ||\n\t\t!maps.Equal(desired.Spec.Template.Annotations, fetched.Spec.Template.Annotations) ||\n\t\tlen(desired.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers) != len(fetched.Spec.Template.Spec.Containers) {\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n```\n\n(`maps` is already imported in `utils.go`)\n\n### File 6: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/controller.go` (MODIFY)\n\nAdd a watch for the CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap so changes to it trigger reconciliation. Add this predicate and watch.\n\nAdd a new predicate (after line 134, the `controllerConfigMapPredicates`):\n\n```go\n\tinjectedCABundleConfigMapPredicate := predicate.NewPredicateFuncs(func(object client.Object) bool {\n\t\treturn object.GetNamespace() == common.OperatorNamespace &&\n\t\t\tobject.GetName() == common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName\n\t})\n```\n\nAdd a new `Watches` line in the builder chain (after the existing ConfigMap watch at line 152):\n\n```go\n\t\tWatches(&corev1.ConfigMap{}, handler.EnqueueRequestsFromMapFunc(mapFunc), builder.WithPredicates(injectedCABundleConfigMapPredicate)).\n```\n\nThe `mapFunc` already handles objects without the expected labels by returning an empty request list. We need a special mapFunc for the injected CM since it won't have the controller's labels. Add this before the builder:\n\n```go\n\tinjectedCABundleMapFunc := func(ctx context.Context, obj client.Object) []reconcile.Request {\n\t\tr.log.V(4).Info(\"received reconcile event for CNO-injected CA bundle\", \"name\", obj.GetName(), \"namespace\", obj.GetNamespace())\n\t\tistiocsrList := &v1alpha1.IstioCSRList{}\n\t\tif err := r.List(ctx, istiocsrList); err != nil {\n\t\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to list IstioCSR resources for CA bundle change\")\n\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar requests []reconcile.Request\n\t\tfor _, item := range istiocsrList.Items {\n\t\t\trequests = append(requests, reconcile.Request{\n\t\t\t\tNamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{\n\t\t\t\t\tName:      item.GetName(),\n\t\t\t\t\tNamespace: item.GetNamespace(),\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn requests\n\t}\n```\n\nAnd use it in the Watches call:\n\n```go\n\t\tWatches(&corev1.ConfigMap{}, handler.EnqueueRequestsFromMapFunc(injectedCABundleMapFunc), builder.WithPredicates(injectedCABundleConfigMapPredicate)).\n```\n\nThe `v1alpha1.IstioCSRList` type is already imported, and `r.List` is available from `CtrlClient`.\n\n### File 7: `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go` (NEW)\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n)\n\nfunc TestComputeCABundleHash(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname      string\n\t\tbundle1   string\n\t\tbundle2   string\n\t\twantEqual bool\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:      \"identical bundles produce same hash\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBfoo\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBfoo\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\twantEqual: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:      \"different bundles produce different hashes\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBfoo\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBbar\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\twantEqual: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:      \"empty vs non-empty produce different hashes\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:   \"\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:   \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBfoo\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\twantEqual: false,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\thash1 := computeCABundleHash(tt.bundle1)\n\t\t\thash2 := computeCABundleHash(tt.bundle2)\n\n\t\t\tif (hash1 == hash2) != tt.wantEqual {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"computeCABundleHash equality = %v, want %v (hash1=%s, hash2=%s)\",\n\t\t\t\t\thash1 == hash2, tt.wantEqual, hash1, hash2)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tif len(hash1) != 64 {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"expected SHA-256 hex length 64, got %d\", len(hash1))\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Commands to run\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-baseline\n\n# Verify it compiles\ngo build ./...\n\n# Run the istiocsr tests\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n\n# Run the full test suite (optional)\nmake test\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary of changes\n\n| File | Action | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go` | **New** | `readTrustedCABundle()`, `computeCABundleHash()`, `stampCABundleHash()` — reads CNO ConfigMap, computes SHA-256 of PEM data |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go` | **Modify** | Add `caContentHashAnnotation` constant |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/install_istiocsr.go` | **Modify** | Call `stampCABundleHash()` before deployment reconciliation, pass hash to `createOrApplyDeployments` |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go` | **Modify** | Accept `caBundleHash` param, stamp it as annotation on `deployment.Spec.Template.Annotations` |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go` | **Modify** | Add `Annotations` comparison to `deploymentSpecModified` — the idempotency guard that skips the update when hash is unchanged |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/controller.go` | **Modify** | Watch the CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap for changes, enqueue all IstioCSR instances on change |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go` | **New** | Unit tests for `computeCABundleHash` |\n\nThe idempotency guard works as follows: when the CA bundle content hasn't changed, `computeCABundleHash` returns the same hash → the pod template annotation is the same → `deploymentSpecModified` returns `false` (via the `maps.Equal` check on annotations) → the `UpdateWithRetry` call is skipped. Only when the PEM content actually changes will the hash differ, causing the deployment to be updated, which triggers a rolling restart because the pod template spec changed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":197,"cache_read_input_tokens":96300,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":197,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c448d4f-0961-417e-862e-16da4dffbcc0","uuid":"3ce95773-fbc8-48df-9eab-e077202a27ae","timestamp":"2026-07-16T13:42:15.640Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5qDqfa4mT7NzywnW4Yn"}
